{"created-date": {"value": 1671613798532}, "last-modified-date": {"value": 1671613798532}, "source": {"source-orcid": {"uri": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9785-7726", "path": "0000-0002-9785-7726", "host": "orcid.org"}, "source-client-id": null, "source-name": {"value": "Luca Baldini"}, "assertion-origin-orcid": null, "assertion-origin-client-id": null, "assertion-origin-name": null}, "put-code": 125080020, "path": "/0000-0002-9785-7726/work/125080020", "title": {"title": {"value": "Observation of Rayleigh-Lamb waves generated by the 2022 Hunga-Tonga volcanic eruption with the POLA detectors at Ny-\u00c5lesund"}, "subtitle": null, "translated-title": null}, "journal-title": {"value": "Scientific Reports"}, "short-description": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title><jats:p>The eruption of the Hunga-Tonga volcano in the South Pacific Ocean on January 15, 2022, at about 4:15 UTC, generated a violent explosion, which created atmospheric pressure disturbances in the form of Rayleigh-Lamb waves detected all over the globe. Here we discuss the observation of the Hunga-Tonga shock-wave performed at the Ny-\u00c5lesund Research Station on the Spitsbergen island, by the detectors of the PolarquEEEst experiment and their ancillary sensors. Online pressure data as well as the results of dedicated offline analysis are presented and discussed in details. Results include wave arrival times, wave amplitude measurements and wave velocity calculation. We observed five passages of the shock wave with a significance larger than 3 <jats:inline-formula><jats:alternatives><jats:tex-math>$$\\sigma$$</jats:tex-math><mml:math xmlns:mml=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n                  <mml:mi>\u03c3</mml:mi>\n                </mml:math></jats:alternatives></jats:inline-formula> and an amplitude up to 1 hPa. The average propagation velocity resulted to be (308 \u00b1 0.6) m/s. Possible effects of the atmospheric pressure variation associated with the shock-wave multiple passages on the cosmic-ray rate at ground level are also investigated. We did not find any significant evidence of this effect.</jats:p>", "citation": {"citation-type": "bibtex", "citation-value": "@article{Abbrescia_2022,\tdoi = {10.1038/s41598-022-23984-2},\turl = {https://doi.org/10.1038%2Fs41598-022-23984-2},\tyear = 2022,\tmonth = {nov},\tpublisher = {Springer Science and Business Media {LLC}},\tvolume = {12},\tnumber = {1},\tauthor = {M. Abbrescia and C. Avanzini and L. Baldini and R. Baldini Ferroli and G. Batignani and M. Battaglieri and S. Boi and E. Bossini and F. Carnesecchi and M. Casula and D. Cavazza and C. Cical{\\`{o}} and L. Cifarelli and F. Coccetti and E. Coccia and A. Corvaglia and D. De Gruttola and S. De Pasquale and L. Galante and M. Garbini and G. Gemme and I. Gnesi and E. Gramstad and S. Grazzi and E. S. Haland and D. Hatzifotiadou and P. La Rocca and Z. Liu and L. Lombardo and G. Mandaglio and A. Margotti and G. Maron and M. N. Mazziotta and M. Mazzola and A. Mulliri and R. Nania and F. Noferini and F. Nozzoli and F. Ould-Saada and F. Palmonari and M. Panareo and M. P. Panetta and R. Paoletti and M. Parvis and C. Pellegrino and L. Perasso and O. Pinazza and C. Pinto and S. Pisano and F. Riggi and G. Righini and C. Ripoli and M. Rizzi and G. Sartorelli and E. Scapparone and M. Schioppa and G. Scioli and A. Scribano and M. Selvi and M. Taiuti and G. Terreni and A. Trifir{\\`{o}} and M. Trimarchi and A. P. Viola and C. Vistoli and L. Votano and M. C. S. Williams and A. Zichichi and R. Zuyeuski},\ttitle = {Observation of Rayleigh-Lamb waves generated by the 2022 Hunga-Tonga volcanic eruption with the {POLA} detectors at Ny-{\\{AA}}lesund},\tjournal = {Scientific Reports}}"}, "type": "journal-article", "publication-date": {"year": {"value": "2022"}, "month": {"value": "11"}, "day": {"value": "20"}}, "external-ids": {"external-id": [{"external-id-type": "doi", "external-id-value": "10.1038/s41598-022-23984-2", "external-id-normalized": {"value": "10.1038/s41598-0